This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during the presentation of the Congressional Gold Medal to Bob Dole, a former senator and American war hero. The President commends Dole for his service and highlights his dedication to fighting for the values of Kansas, veterans, the disabled, and all Americans. Trump also mentions Dole's role in organizing Honor Flights for World War II veterans to visit the memorial in Washington, D.C. The President emphasizes the importance of honoring and remembering the sacrifices made by veterans, and praises Dole as a patriot, hero, and leader. The article concludes with Trump expressing gratitude to Dole for his service and congratulating him on receiving the Congressional Gold Medal.